[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare care coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: care-episode initiation, longitudinal-state management, channel entry, input safety screening with continuous-emergency-screening, identity-and-context loading, conversation handling with multi-system tool use, output safety screening, escalation routing including warm handoff to human coordinators, care-team reporting, and outcome correlation. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones: multi-system integration governance, care-episode-tracking as durable state, coordination-protocol-as-code with clinical-leadership ownership, in-network-verification as architectural primitive, and human-coordinator-handoff as first-class capability.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CARE-EPISODE INITIATION ───────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Initiating clinical event]                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Hospital discharge with follow-up requirements       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - ED discharge with follow-up requirements             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - New diagnosis requiring multi-specialist coordination│
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Oncology treatment plan initiation                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Transplant evaluation initiation                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pediatric complex-care diagnosis                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Frequent-utilizer flag from analytics                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Episode instantiation]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Episode type selected from protocol library          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Open follow-up items captured from discharge         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      summary, care plan, or order set                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active referrals linked                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active prior-authorizations linked                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient's stated coverage information validated      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Episode protocol applied (target time windows for    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      each follow-up, escalation criteria, out-of-bounds   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      conditions)                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient introduction]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - First outreach scheduled per episode-type protocol   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (often within 24 hours post-discharge)               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Channel preferences applied                          │
