[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-system integration governance.** Each integration (scheduling, referral, prior-auth, eligibility, EHR, pharmacy, lab, imaging, case-management) has a managed contract with specific authentication, error handling, rate limits, and a designated owner on both the assistant team and the system-of-record team. Integration breakage is a launch-gate-blocking event.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-episode-tracking as durable state.** The episode is the central abstraction. Episode events (initiation, follow-up-completion, deviation-detected, escalation, completion) are first-class events in the EventBridge bus.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Coordination-protocol-as-code with clinical-leadership ownership.** Each episode type has a structured protocol owned by the appropriate clinical leadership (hospital medicine for post-discharge, ED leadership for post-ED, oncology for cancer episodes, etc.), reviewed annually, and re-reviewed when material clinical updates occur.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **In-network-verification as architectural primitive.** Surprise-bill prevention is a top-three failure mode the assistant prevents. In-network verification runs before any scheduling action and is surfaced explicitly to the patient.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Human-coordinator-handoff as first-class capability.** The handoff to a human coordinator is not an afterthought; it is a designed product feature with case-management-software integration. The coordinator's workflow on the receiving end shapes the bot's handoff payload.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-bot intent routing.** The assistant is the chapter's most likely first contact for complex-care patients. Routing across recipes 11.2-11.8 is a discipline, not an exception. The patient's conversation context follows the routing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Continuous emergency screening across every utterance.** Same as the triage bot and the chronic disease coach. Acute emergencies route immediately; the assistant does not try to handle them in-conversation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every statement about an appointment, referral, prior auth, or benefit cites the source-of-truth system response. Citations are structured and audit records preserve the citation trail.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-team reporting as first-class capability.** Real-time alerts, weekly digests, monthly summaries, and quarterly clinical-review packets are part of production scope, not phase-2 enhancements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Outcome correlation as core post-launch commitment.** The assistant's clinical performance is bounded by what can be measured against actual outcomes (appointment completion, prior-auth initiation, surprise-bill rate, readmission rate, patient-reported experience). Multi-quarter post-launch work.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement rate, escalation rate, citation-coverage rate, outcome metrics, and patient satisfaction vary by language, channel, episode type, age cohort, payer, and social-determinant flags.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When any source-of-truth integration is unreachable, the assistant degrades gracefully: "I'm having trouble checking that right now; let me connect you to a coordinator who can help." The graceful degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
